            . I was opposite the north door of <placeName id="t18300916-148-crimeloc772">St. Paul's cathedral</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-148-crimeloc772" type="placeName" value="St. Paul's cathedral"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-148-crimeloc772" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-148-off770 t18300916-148-crimeloc772"></join>, about two o'clock, on the 19th of July - I felt a pressure on my pocket, looked round, and saw the prisoner transferring my handkerchief to a companion, but he dropped it on the pavement, and I took it up; this is it - it is mine; I am quite sure the prisoner dropped it - I had used it a minute or two before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-148-person1276">
                  THOMAS 
                  WAGSTAFF
               <interp inst="t18300916-148-person1276" type="surname" value="WAGSTAFF"></interp>
